STA Report — synth_top
Tool    : Yosys 0.9 (git sha1 1979e0b)
Target  : SKY130 HD  @  200 MHz (5.0 ns period)
Date    : Spring 2026 | ECE 410/510 HW4AI CF07

NOTE: Formal STA (OpenSTA) not available in Yosys 0.9.
      This report summarizes the LTP (longest topological path) output.
      Setup slack values require OpenSTA with mapped SKY130 liberty -- planned for M3.

=== LONGEST TOPOLOGICAL PATH (ltp) ===

Total depth : 192 nodes
Source      : \s_axis_tvalid (primary input)
Sink        : \pipe_data[7] [0] = m_axis_tdata[0] (primary output)

Path summary by pipeline stage:
  [0-1]   AXI handshake: s_axis_tvalid -> $logic_and
  [2-129] S1 input latch: pipe_data[0] mux+DFF chain (64 bits x 2 nodes = 128)
  [130]   S1->S2 boundary: pipe_data[1] DFF
  [131]   S2 running_max: $alu (compare + subtract, 9 ALU cells)
  [132]   S2->S3: $ternary exp LUT index select
  [133]   S3 exp LUT: exp_beat lookup
  [134]   S3->S4: pipe_data[2] DFF
  [136]   S4 beat_sum: $macc (8-input adder fused)
  [137]   S4->accumulate: $ternary running_sum mux
  [138-185] S4 running_sum DFF chain (24 bits x 2 nodes = 48)
  [186]   S5 start: $ne zero-check on running_sum
  [187]   S5 normalize: norm_beat via $div (8 dividers, CRITICAL PATH)
  [188-189] S5->S6: pipe_data[4] DFF
  [190]   S6: pipe_data[5] DFF
  [191]   S7: pipe_data[6] DFF
  [192]   S8: pipe_data[7] DFF (output)

Note on loop warnings:
  Yosys LTP reported loops on pipe_data[0], running_sum, running_max.
  These are FALSE ALARMS caused by Yosys 0.9 traversing DFF outputs
  back through procmux feedback before cutting at clock edge.
  synth_netlist.v confirms no actual combinational cycles exist.
  The true loop source is: assign s_axis_tready = m_axis_tready | ~pipe_valid[0]
  (AXI back-pressure, not a design error).

=== TIMING ESTIMATE (no liberty mapping) ===

Critical combinational path per clock cycle:
  running_sum[23:0] DFF output
  -> $ne zero-check (~1 gate)
  -> $div x8 (unsigned 24-bit division, dominant term)
  -> norm_beat[63:0]
  -> pipe_data[4] DFF input

SKY130 HD 24-bit divider estimated delay: 8-12 ns at TT/25C/1.8V
=> Design does NOT close timing at 200 MHz (5 ns) with $div cells.
=> Closing timing at 100 MHz (10 ns) is possible after replacing
   $div with reciprocal multiply (M3 plan).

